09/09/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bosnian Serb Agriculture Minister Rodoljub Trkulja said Monday (8 September) that the severe three-month drought has devastated the entity's corn, wheat and potato crops.
Damage from the summer heat wave has been assessed at one-quarter of Republika Srpska's total budget.
In Bulgaria, meanwhile, officials reported that the Danube's water level has fallen to new record lows.
At Ruse, the river fell to 73cm below ground level, beating the 57cm record set on 30 August.
(AFP - 08/09/03)
